ZCZC GE59
EXTENDED OUTLOOK
SUNDAY TO WEDNESDAY
ISSUED BY THE MET OFFICE ON BEHALF OF THE MARITIME AND COASTGUARD AGENCY
AT 062300 UTC
LOW 997 TRACKS SLWY NE ACROSS THE NERN N SEA THROUGH SUNDAY NIGHT WHILE
SLWY FLN. THE LOW EXPANDS ACROSS THE NORWEGIAN BASIN AND WERN SCANDINAVIA
THROUGH MONDAY AND MAINTAINS A TROUGH SWARDS ACROSS THE SERN N SEA. THIS
TROUGH TRACKS E ACROSS DENMARK ON TUESDAY AND THE LOW LOSES ITS IDENTITY
AS A WEAK RIDGE OF HIGH PRESSURE BUILDS N ACROSS THE BRITISH ISLES. THE RIDGE
THEN TOPPLES E ACROSS THE N SEA ON WEDNESDAY AND HIGH PRESSURE BECOMES ESTABLISHED
ACROSS THE NEAR CONTINENT. AN ATLANTIC LOW PUSHES A FRONTAL TROUGH NE ACROSS
NWERN UK LATER ON WEDNESDAY. THERE IS SOME UNCERTAINTY OVER THE TRACK AND
DEPTH OF THE N SEA LOW AND ITS ASSOCIATED TROUGH SO SOME CHANGES IN THE
FCST ARE LIKELY OVER THE NXT 24 HOURS. NEAR GALE FORCE SW WINDS MAY DEVELOP
ACROSS THE ENGLISH CHANNEL AND SERN N SEA THROUGH SUNDAY EVENING
